courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students will be able to:

1. Grasp the distinctive features of different kinds and types of play:

2. Understand the values of play in developing children holistically;
3. Promote play through staging playful environment;
4. Design play-based curriculum; and

5. Assessing children’s learning in and through play.

courses.course_syllabus:
The course will cover the following topics:

1. history and nature of play;
2. theories and practices of play;
3. values of play for cognitive and social emotional development;
4. play and creative expression in art and music;
5. drama and play;
6. indoor and outdoor play;
7. play and technology

8. teachers’ role in play;
9. play environment and resources;
10. designing play-based curriculum; and

11. assessing play and children’s development.

本科的課程內容包括：
1. 遊戲的歷史和性質；

2. 遊戲的理論和實踐；

3. 遊戲對認知和社會情緒發展的價值；

4. 遊戲與藝術和音樂的創意表達；

5. 戲劇和遊戲；

6. 戶內和戶外的遊戲；

7. 遊戲與科技；

8. 教師在遊戲中的角色；

9. 遊戲的環境和資源；

10. 遊戲為本的課程設計；及

11. 遊戲中幼兒發展的評估。

courses.learning_outcomes:
At the end of the course, students are expected to:

1. compare and contrast different theories of language and literacy development in young children;
2. describe the stages of language development in young children;
3. explain how young children develop language through engagement with other people and their surroundings; and

4. critique current local practices in developing young children’s language and literacy ability.

